This man, as Public Safety Director of Cleveland, controversially ordered the burning of its shanty
towns in response to the Cleveland Torso Murderer. This man co-wrote a memoir with Oscar Farley
which was named for a term coined by Charles Schwarz. George Johnson appointed this man to head
a group dedicated to prosecuting criminals under the Volstead Act. This man’s inability to be bribed
by the Chicago Outfit led him and his men to be labeled the “Untouchables.” For the point, name this
Prohibition-era crime fighter who helped bring down Al Capone.=====
Eliot Ness
